00:37.203 --> 00:41.166
[♪...]

00:54.137 --> 00:55.305
Girl: GOOD MORNING, FINGER.

00:55.388 --> 00:57.015
ONE-TWO-THREE-FOUR-FIVE-SIX.

00:57.098 --> 00:59.476
SEVEN-EIGHT-NINE-10-11-12-13-14,
15-16-18-90-100.

00:59.559 --> 01:03.980
HONEYBEE TROOP 828, BESSIE
HIGGENBOTTOM REPORTING FOR DUTY.

01:04.063 --> 01:04.397
[GRUNTS]

01:04.480 --> 01:08.943
[♪...]

01:09.027 --> 01:10.195
HI, MOM, BYE, MOM.

01:10.278 --> 01:12.489
HAVE FUN, SWEETIE.

01:12.572 --> 01:13.990
{\an3}ARE YOU GOING TO
YOUR TROOP MEETING?

01:14.073 --> 01:15.283
CAN I COME?

01:17.994 --> 01:22.582
NO...

01:24.626 --> 01:26.669
BESSIE...

01:26.753 --> 01:27.629
HI, BESSIE.

01:27.712 --> 01:28.755
HI, YOU GUYS.

01:29.798 --> 01:33.384
[CHUCKLES] YO, BESSIE.

01:33.468 --> 01:35.220
'SUP.

01:42.811 --> 01:45.188
♪ LONG PAN, LONG- ♪ HUH?

01:45.271 --> 01:46.564
[BESSIE GRUNTS]

01:46.648 --> 01:50.360
SO, MIGHTY B.,
WE MEET AGAIN.

01:50.443 --> 01:54.030
{\an3}PREPARE TO TASTE THE AWESOME
STING OF THE MIGHTY B.

01:54.113 --> 01:57.700
[FIGHTING GRUNTS...]

01:57.784 --> 02:03.540
[GRUNTING...]

02:04.415 --> 02:08.002
{\an1}Man: SO YOU'VE WON
THIS TIME, MIGHTY B.

02:08.086 --> 02:12.298
AND I HONOR YOU WITH
THIS FRESH DUMPLING.

02:12.382 --> 02:14.050
{\an1}[CHUCKLES]

02:14.133 --> 02:17.262
{\an1}Bessie: THANKS, MR. WU,
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

02:17.345 --> 02:19.055
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:19.138 --> 02:19.806
HI, ROCKY, AWESOME MOVES.

02:19.889 --> 02:22.308
OH, HEY, BESSIE. [GRUNTS]

02:22.392 --> 02:24.227
WANT TO HANG OUT WITH US?

02:24.310 --> 02:27.480
{\an5}SORRY, ROCKY, I WISH I COULD
STOP, BUT I CAN'T, BUT I'LL
SEE YOU LATER...

02:27.564 --> 02:27.939
{\an1}OH, MAN.

02:28.022 --> 02:29.816
Bessie: OH...

02:29.899 --> 02:30.567
WHOA...

02:30.650 --> 02:33.570
[SCREAMS...]

02:33.653 --> 02:37.407
[♪...]

02:37.490 --> 02:39.701
MWAH, MWAH.

02:39.784 --> 02:40.743
[GRUNTS]

02:40.827 --> 02:41.744
[GRUNTING]

02:41.828 --> 02:42.745
OH, THAT'S GONNA HURT.

02:42.829 --> 02:47.041
[GRUNTING...]

02:47.125 --> 02:50.753
[SCOFFS] NICE FLIGHT, MIGHTY B.

02:50.837 --> 02:54.465
[GASPS] OH, MY GOSH, A PUPPY.

02:54.549 --> 02:55.174
PUPPY, PUPPY, PUPPY, PUPPY.

02:55.258 --> 02:56.259
WHO'S A PUPPY, WHO'S A PUPPY?

02:56.342 --> 03:00.597
PRECIOUS IS A DOG,
"MESSY" HIGGENBOTTOM, OK?

03:00.680 --> 03:02.932
A PUREBRED.

03:03.016 --> 03:05.935
{\an3}I'M TRAINING HER FOR
THE HONEYBEE DOG SHOW.

03:06.019 --> 03:08.313
HONEYBEE DOG SHOW?

03:08.396 --> 03:10.064
WHAT, WHAT HONEYBEE DOG SHOW?

03:10.148 --> 03:12.609
THE ONE PORTIA'S MOM
IS PUTTING ON, SEE?

03:12.692 --> 03:14.986
Bessie: WHAT?

03:15.069 --> 03:17.155
{\an3}Girl: THE WINNER GETS
THE ANIMAL APPRECIATION BADGE.

03:17.238 --> 03:18.323
PORTIA'S MOM SAID.

03:18.406 --> 03:20.325
OH...

03:20.408 --> 03:21.618
[SCOFFS]

03:21.701 --> 03:24.621
OH, YOU DIDN'T
GET THE BEE-MAIL, HUH?

03:24.704 --> 03:26.122
[GRUNTS] BUT YOU DON'T
HAVE A DOG ANYWAY, BESSIE.

03:26.205 --> 03:28.499
GUESS YOU'RE NOT GONNA
GET THE BADGE THIS TIME.

03:28.583 --> 03:30.501
[EXPLOSION]

03:30.585 --> 03:32.170
ONE, I'VE ALWAYS WANTED A DOG.

03:32.253 --> 03:36.299
{\an4}TWO, IF I GET ONE NOW, I CAN
TEACH IT TRICKS AND I CAN PUT IT
IN THE HONEYBEE DOG SHOW

03:36.382 --> 03:38.134
{\an1}AND THEN IT'LL WIN
THE ANIMAL APPRECIATION BADGE

03:38.217 --> 03:39.761
{\an4}AND THAT IS A BADGE THAT
I REALLY-REALLY-REALLY-
REALLY-REALLY WANT.

03:39.844 --> 03:42.639
{\an3}45, IF WE GOT A DOG,
IT COULD GUARD OUR APARTMENT.

03:42.722 --> 03:45.058
46, DOGS ARE NICE.

03:45.141 --> 03:46.601
47, DOGS AREN'T CATS.

03:46.684 --> 03:48.978
{\an6}48, WHEN YOU'RE TIRED,
YOU CAN REST YOUR HEAD ON IT
LIKE A PILLOW.

03:49.062 --> 03:52.857
{\an3}729, IF I GOT A DOG,
I WOULD RESCUE IT.

03:52.941 --> 03:56.319
{\an6}AND THERE ARE OVER 3,812
HOMELESS ANIMALS IN THE CITY OF
SAN FRANCISCO.

03:56.402 --> 03:58.738
{\an6}WOULDN'T THAT BE GREAT, MOM,
WOULDN'T THAT BE GREAT IF I
RESCUED A LONELY DOG?

03:58.821 --> 04:02.116
YES, BESSIE, YES, GO.

04:02.200 --> 04:04.369
RESCUE A DOG.

04:04.452 --> 04:07.705
{\an1}BUT YOU HAVE TO
TAKE YOUR BROTHER.

04:07.789 --> 04:08.831
[FOGHORN BLOWS]

04:08.915 --> 04:10.041
[GLASS BREAKING]

04:10.124 --> 04:13.586
Man: HEY, GET BACK HERE,
THAT'S MY LUNCH.

04:16.880 --> 04:19.634
[BURPS]

04:19.716 --> 04:22.845
{\an1}Brother: BESSIE, WAIT,
DON'T WALK SO FAST.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.931
BEN, I HAPPEN TO BE
ON A BADGE MISSION.

04:25.014 --> 04:26.933
I HAVE AN ANIMAL TO RESCUE.

04:27.016 --> 04:29.477
I KNOW, I CAN HELP.

04:29.560 --> 04:30.645
{\an3}EVERY SUPERHERO NEEDS
A SIDEKICK.

04:30.728 --> 04:33.564
[SCOFFS]

04:33.648 --> 04:35.858
I'M NOT THE MIGHTY B. YET, BEN.

04:35.942 --> 04:39.737
I STILL HAVE 4,584 BADGES TO GO.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.073
AND I WORK ALONE.

04:42.156 --> 04:43.574
[GASPS]

04:43.658 --> 04:45.159
BESSIE, LOOK.

04:50.289 --> 04:52.500
Bessie: SCRATCH,
SCRATCH, SCRATCH.

04:52.583 --> 04:54.043
[DOG GRUNTS]

04:54.127 --> 04:55.044
Bessie: HI...

04:55.128 --> 04:58.214
I'M BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM, AND...

04:58.298 --> 05:01.467
{\an3}[GASPS] LOOK AT YOUR
TORN EAR, AWESOME.

05:01.551 --> 05:02.885
I HATE PERFECT EARS.

05:02.969 --> 05:05.013
I HATE PERFECT ANYTHINGS.

05:05.096 --> 05:09.058
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO BE MY DOG?

05:09.142 --> 05:11.185
[LAUGHS] I'M GONNA
TAKE THAT AS A YES.

05:11.269 --> 05:12.395
YOU'RE A HAPPY DOG, HUH?

05:12.478 --> 05:15.356
OH, MAN, YOU'RE SO HAPPY
I'M GONNA NAME YOU HAPPY.

05:15.440 --> 05:18.484
{\an5}AND GUESS WHAT,
IT KEEPS GETTING BETTER,
YOU'RE GONNA BE IN A DOG SHOW.

05:18.568 --> 05:21.029
[YOWLS]

05:22.905 --> 05:25.241
{\an5}Bessie: THE ONLY ONE
IN THE DOG SHOW THAT I'M REALLY
WORRIED ABOUT

05:25.324 --> 05:27.493
IS PRECIOUS, PORTIA'S DOG,
THAT I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.203
{\an1}BUT I THINK WE HAVE AN EXCELLENT
CHANCE OF WINNING THE BADGE.

05:29.287 --> 05:31.956
{\an1}I MADE UP THIS WHOLE
TRAINING SCHEDULE.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.167
{\an4}IT'S COLOR-CODED,
AND I USED THOSE MARKERS
THAT SMELL LIKE CANDY.

05:34.250 --> 05:37.378
BUT THEY DON'T TASTE LIKE CANDY.

05:37.462 --> 05:41.215
ANYWAY, FIRST I'M GONNA
TEACH YOU DOG OBEDIENCE.

05:41.299 --> 05:43.926
STAY, STAY, STAY.

05:44.010 --> 05:48.639
STAY, STAY, STAY, STAY.

05:48.723 --> 05:52.435
{\an3}STAY...

05:52.518 --> 05:54.479
STAY, STAY, STAY, STAY, STAY.

05:54.562 --> 05:57.940
HOW TO FETCH...

05:58.024 --> 06:00.276
AND HOW TO BALLROOM DANCE.

06:00.359 --> 06:04.405
MAY I HAVE THIS WALTZ, GOOD SIR?

06:09.202 --> 06:11.662
{\an3}[PANTING]

06:11.746 --> 06:13.998
{\an3}HAPPY, WHAT'S THAT
BEHIND YOUR EAR?

06:14.082 --> 06:18.461
[GASPS] A FRESH DOG BISCUIT.

06:18.544 --> 06:20.755
AND IT'S MADE WITH LOVE.

06:20.838 --> 06:22.006
{\an3}GOOD BOY.

06:22.090 --> 06:25.259
NOW SHOW ME YOUR STUFF.

06:25.343 --> 06:27.303
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

06:27.387 --> 06:29.138
HE'S THE WORST DOG I EVER MET.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.431
{\an3}[GASPS]

06:30.515 --> 06:31.933
YOU'RE SIX!

06:32.016 --> 06:34.018
HOW MANY DOGS HAVE YOU MET?

06:34.102 --> 06:35.853
{\an1}HAPPY'S THE BEST DOG
IN THE WHOLE WORLD

06:35.937 --> 06:37.897
AND I JUST KNOW HE'S GONNA
WIN THE DOG SHOW TOMORROW

06:37.980 --> 06:40.817
{\an1}AND I'M GONNA GET THE ANIMAL
APPRECIATION BADGE.

06:44.070 --> 06:45.822
{\an1}Woman: HERE'S A LITTLE
"TOKEN OF OUR APPRECIATION."

06:45.905 --> 06:48.199
{\an1}PORTIA AND I PUT IT
TOGETHER FOR YOU.

06:48.282 --> 06:51.828
YES, I AM <i> NOT</i> NOT TAKING THIS.

06:51.911 --> 06:54.330
[BOTH LAUGHING]

06:54.413 --> 06:58.376
{\an1}[GASPS] PORTIA, PRECIOUS
LOOKS SO PRETTY.

06:58.459 --> 07:00.044
[SCOFFS] LIKE I DON'T KNOW THAT.

07:00.128 --> 07:01.546
LIKE SHE DON'T KNOW THAT.

07:01.629 --> 07:04.590
INTRODUCING HAPPY HIGGENBOTTOM.

07:04.674 --> 07:05.842
{\an3}[HISSES]

07:05.925 --> 07:07.009
[GROWLS]

07:07.093 --> 07:09.011
HE'S A SHOW DOG AS WELL.

07:09.095 --> 07:12.140
THAT FILTHY OLD THING?

07:12.223 --> 07:13.975
WHERE'D YOU GET HIM, A SHELTER?

07:14.058 --> 07:16.018
{\an3}WITH ALL THE DIRTY PEOPLE
AND THE DIRTY THINGS?

07:16.102 --> 07:20.439
SHE FOUND HIM
IN A DUMPSTER. [LAUGHS]

07:20.523 --> 07:21.899
HAPPY, WAIT.

07:21.983 --> 07:24.527
{\an5}[AUDIENCE GASPS]

07:21.983 --> 07:24.527
Bessie: WAIT, WHERE ARE
YOU GOING?

07:28.072 --> 07:30.449
{\an5}[SNARLING...]

07:28.072 --> 07:30.449
{\an3}YIPE.

07:35.371 --> 07:36.998
HAPPY, WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU?

07:37.081 --> 07:39.041
WE'RE ON IN FIVE MINUTES, BOY.

07:39.125 --> 07:43.462
[BARKING AND SNARLING]

07:43.546 --> 07:46.132
{\an1}HEY, FIRST OF ALL, HAPPY,
WE DO NOT USE WORDS LIKE THAT.

07:46.215 --> 07:48.551
{\an1}SECOND, I DIDN'T KNOW THAT
YOU HATED DOG SHOWS.

07:48.634 --> 07:51.888
[BARKING]

07:51.971 --> 07:54.265
HAPPY, LANGUAGE.

07:54.348 --> 07:55.808
WAIT, YOU WANT YOUR OLD LIFE
BACK, DON'T YOU?

07:55.892 --> 07:58.477
[WHINES]

07:58.561 --> 08:00.771
[SIGHS] I GET IT.

08:00.855 --> 08:02.481
YOU DON'T WANT TO BE TIED DOWN.

08:02.565 --> 08:04.025
WELL, I'M NOT GONNA BE
YOUR BEAST OF BURDEN.

08:04.108 --> 08:06.569
YOU CAN GO, HAPPY.

08:06.652 --> 08:07.904
{\an1}FLY FREE.

08:07.987 --> 08:10.031
SING OUT LOUD.

08:10.114 --> 08:12.909
{\an1}WRITE IF YOU CAN-
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

08:12.992 --> 08:16.746
LEAVE, I DON'T WANT TO SEE
YOUR FACE- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

08:16.829 --> 08:18.456
YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND.

08:18.539 --> 08:20.875
I DON'T NEED ANYBODY,
I'LL DO THIS THING BY MYSELF.

08:20.958 --> 08:22.001
BEAT IT.

08:22.084 --> 08:24.337
STAY, PLEASE.

08:24.420 --> 08:27.089
GET OUT OF HERE.

08:27.173 --> 08:29.467
[SIGHS]

08:29.550 --> 08:31.552
WHAT?

08:31.636 --> 08:34.639
[SCOFFS] THAT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY, BUT...

08:34.722 --> 08:36.097
I KNOW, BUT...

08:36.182 --> 08:39.477
OH, YOU'RE RIGHT, FINGER.

08:39.559 --> 08:41.520
I GOTTA LET THIS ONE GO.

08:41.604 --> 08:46.359
Audience: OOH...

08:50.154 --> 08:52.698
"LOOK AT ME, I'M HIGH-FASHION."

08:52.782 --> 08:57.828
[MUSIC PLAYS IN DISTANCE...]

08:57.912 --> 08:59.580
Bessie: SCRATCH,
SCRATCH, SCRATCH.

09:02.083 --> 09:05.169
[LAUGHS] I KNEW YOU HAD AN ACE.

09:05.253 --> 09:08.130
MADE WITH LOVE.

09:08.214 --> 09:11.759
[SNARLING]

09:11.842 --> 09:12.969
[PANTING]

09:13.052 --> 09:15.805
[SCOFFS]

09:15.888 --> 09:17.807
AREN'T THEY ADORABLE, FOLKS?

09:17.890 --> 09:19.350
{\an3}LOOKS LIKE WE'VE GOT
A WINNER, HUH?

09:19.433 --> 09:22.311
AND NOW FOR
OUR LAST CONTESTANTS.

09:22.395 --> 09:25.189
BESSIE AND HAPPY HIGGENBOTTOM.

09:31.195 --> 09:33.656
HI, HI.

09:33.739 --> 09:35.825
MY NAME IS BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM.

09:35.908 --> 09:41.497
[CLEARS THROAT] AND HAPPY SENDS
HIS SINCERE REGRETS

09:41.580 --> 09:45.668
BUT WE HAVE MUTUALLY DECIDED,
UH, TO PART WAYS....

09:45.751 --> 09:46.836
[AUDIENCE GASPS]

09:46.919 --> 09:50.006
...AS COMMITTED
AND CARING FRIENDS.

09:50.089 --> 09:52.466
[DOG BARKING]

09:52.550 --> 09:55.011
[GASPS] HAPPY?

09:55.094 --> 09:56.846
[BARKING]

09:56.929 --> 09:58.389
OH...

09:58.472 --> 10:02.310
AND, [BREATHES HEAVILY],
HE... IS NO LONGER...

10:02.393 --> 10:05.271
{\an5}[FEEDBACK WHINES]

10:02.393 --> 10:05.271
...MY DOG.

10:05.354 --> 10:06.856
[AUDIENCE GASPS]

10:06.939 --> 10:08.149
[BARKING AND PANTING]

10:08.232 --> 10:10.943
[BARKING...]

10:11.027 --> 10:12.862
HAPPY.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.613
YOU CAME BACK.

10:14.697 --> 10:16.407
{\an3}[BARKS]

10:16.490 --> 10:19.744
YOU WANT TO DO THE DOG SHOW?

10:19.827 --> 10:20.911
GIVE ME A BEAT, FELLOWS.

10:23.497 --> 10:27.460
[AUDIENCE CHEERS]

10:36.218 --> 10:39.722
[♪...]

10:43.684 --> 10:45.353
{\an5}[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

10:43.684 --> 10:45.353
[AUDIENCE CHANTS "BESSIE..."]

10:45.436 --> 10:48.397
WELL, THIS WASN'T THE PLAN.

10:48.481 --> 10:50.399
DON'T BLOW IT.

10:50.483 --> 10:53.319
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:53.402 --> 10:55.654
{\an1}PLEASE, YOU'RE JUST
REPEATING YOURSELVES.

10:55.738 --> 10:59.617
{\an1}NOW THEN, IT'S...
IT'S A... IT'S A TIE.

10:59.700 --> 11:02.286
BETWEEN PRECIOUS AND HAPPY.

11:02.370 --> 11:04.705
Audience: BOO...

11:04.789 --> 11:06.415
Judge: SHUSH, ZIP IT.

11:06.499 --> 11:10.336
I, THE JUDGE,
THE ULTIMATE AUTHORITY

11:10.419 --> 11:14.298
WILL DECIDE A WINNER BASED UPON
THE DOG'S BREEDING.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.550
THE YOUNG LADIES, PLEASE BRING
THEIR DOGS TO MY TABLE.

11:16.634 --> 11:17.093
LET'S SEE HERE.

11:17.176 --> 11:19.095
UGH.

11:19.178 --> 11:21.472
TYPICAL.

11:21.555 --> 11:23.516
HE'S JUST A BEAT-UP MUTT.

11:23.599 --> 11:25.267
PRECIOUS WINS.

11:25.351 --> 11:26.644
[AUDIENCE GASPS]

11:26.727 --> 11:30.398
{\an1}[SIGHS]

11:30.481 --> 11:31.607
{\an1}JUST SO YOU KNOW,
I'M FINE WITH LOSING.

11:31.690 --> 11:35.694
{\an4}HAPPY'S ONE OF A KIND
AND HE'S MY FRIEND
AND I LOVE HIM.

11:35.778 --> 11:37.863
{\an5}AND HE LOVES ME.

11:35.778 --> 11:37.863
[NEEDLE SCRATCHES OFF RECORD]

11:37.947 --> 11:39.990
{\an1}DON'T FORGET TO
TIP YOUR WAITRESSES.

11:40.074 --> 11:41.409
{\an5}Rocky: THAT'S RIGHT, YEAH.

11:40.074 --> 11:41.409
[AUDIENCE BOOS]

11:41.492 --> 11:43.202
THAT'S REAL ANIMAL APPRECIATION
IF YOU ASK ME.

11:43.285 --> 11:46.288
BUT THIS IS A <i> REAL</i> SHOW DOG.

11:46.372 --> 11:49.083
{\an1}Judge: SEE THIS GORGEOUS
SET OF CHOPPERS?

11:49.166 --> 11:49.875
{\an1}[SHRIEKS]

11:49.959 --> 11:53.254
THAT'S NOT A DOG,
THAT'S A RAT!

11:53.337 --> 11:55.297
[SCREAMS AND GIBBERS]

11:55.381 --> 11:58.968
[GASPS AND STAMMERS]

11:59.051 --> 12:01.262
[GASPING]

12:01.345 --> 12:03.264
{\an1}[LAUGHS] LOOK, EVERYBODY,
SHE KISSED A RAT.

12:03.347 --> 12:06.183
RAT KISSER, OH...

12:06.267 --> 12:09.019
GIVE ME THAT.

12:09.103 --> 12:12.690
ONLY 4,583 BADGES TO GO.

12:12.773 --> 12:13.899
AWESOME, WE'RE SO CLOSE.

12:15.860 --> 12:20.573
[♪...]

12:25.411 --> 12:27.329
AH, YEAH... [LAUGHS]

12:27.413 --> 12:33.627
WHOO-HOO, WHOA...

12:33.711 --> 12:36.881
WHOA-OH-OH-OH, YAY...

12:36.964 --> 12:37.756
HOW'S MY FORM, YOU GUYS?

12:37.840 --> 12:40.509
{\an1}ARMS OUT LIKE THIS,
OR MORE OF A "V"?

12:40.593 --> 12:42.887
MY ARM IS GETTING TIRED.

12:42.970 --> 12:43.971
THAT'S FINE, YOU CAN STOP.

12:45.473 --> 12:46.724
{\an5}YOU KNOW, BEN...

12:45.473 --> 12:46.724
{\an3}[GRUNTS]

12:46.807 --> 12:49.018
I WOULDN'T EXPECT YOU
TO BE ABLE TO CHANNEL

12:49.101 --> 12:51.312
THE ADRENALINE AND FORTITUDE
NECESSARY TO TRAIN FOR

12:51.395 --> 12:54.023
THE ROLLER COASTER EXTRAVAGANZA
THAT IS THE PUNISHER.

12:54.106 --> 12:56.400
AW, YEAH, I CAN FEEL IT.

12:56.484 --> 12:59.278
WHO'S TALL ENOUGH,
WHO'S TALL ENOUGH?

12:59.361 --> 13:00.696
THIS IS THE YEAR, YOU GUYS.

13:00.779 --> 13:02.364
{\an1}BUCKET.

13:03.949 --> 13:06.911
{\an1}[HEAVING]

13:06.994 --> 13:10.247
{\an4}IT'S A PRECAUTION IN
THE HIGHLY-UNLIKELY EVENT
THAT I HAVE A VOMITING EPISODE.

13:10.331 --> 13:14.585
LET'S DO THIS.

13:14.668 --> 13:16.712
[GRUNTS]

13:16.795 --> 13:18.631
[BIRD SHRIEKS]

13:18.714 --> 13:24.970
[♪...]

13:25.054 --> 13:28.432
BEHOLD ITS MAJESTY.

13:28.516 --> 13:32.353
THE PUNISHER.

13:32.436 --> 13:35.189
{\an3}SORRY, BUDDY, WE HAD SOME
GOOD YEARS, LIL' PUN.

13:35.272 --> 13:37.399
I'M HERE TODAY BECAUSE OF YOU.

13:37.483 --> 13:40.653
BUT YOU KNOW PEOPLE GROW UP.

13:40.736 --> 13:42.154
IT'S TIME TO MOVE ON.

13:44.114 --> 13:45.407
[HORN BEEPS]

13:45.491 --> 13:47.201
HI, YOU GUYS.

13:47.284 --> 13:48.494
{\an3}ARE YOU READY TO
ROCK THIS BAD BOY?

13:48.577 --> 13:50.287
[SCOFFS] READY?

13:50.371 --> 13:52.039
{\an1}I'M WEARING DOUBLE-SCRUNCHIES,
AREN'T I? [SCOFFS]

13:52.122 --> 13:55.376
{\an3}BETTER TAKE A MIND PICTURE
WITH YOUR MIND, LADIES

13:55.459 --> 13:56.752
{\an3}'CAUSE WE'RE NEVER GONNA
FORGET THIS DAY.

13:58.963 --> 14:00.214
{\an1}Man: NEXT.

14:00.297 --> 14:01.173
[GASPS]

14:01.257 --> 14:05.427
NEXT... NEXT...

14:05.511 --> 14:08.806
{\an3}CH-CH-CH-CH, GO, BEES,
GO, BEES, WHOOP.

14:08.889 --> 14:10.683
CH-CH-CH-CH,
GO, BEES, GO, BEES.

14:10.766 --> 14:13.310
{\an3}CH-CH-CH-CH,
GO, BEES, GO, BEES.

14:13.394 --> 14:17.189
{\an6}CH-CH-CH-CH, CH-CH-CH-CH,
GO, BEES, GO, BEES,
WHAT'S THAT, ONE MORE TIME?

14:17.273 --> 14:20.109
{\an3}CH-CH-CH-CH, CH-CH-CH-CH,
GO, BEES, GO, BEES.

14:20.192 --> 14:22.444
{\an3}RIDE THE ROLLER COASTER,
UNH. [BEAT BOXES]

14:22.528 --> 14:24.405
[BEAT BOXING]

14:24.488 --> 14:25.823
{\an3}DO YOU WANT TO RIDE ON
THE ROLLER COASTER?

14:25.906 --> 14:27.449
{\an1}YES, I WANT TO RIDE ON
THE ROLLER COASTER.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.285
I SAID WHAT. [BEAT BOXES]

14:29.368 --> 14:31.579
AND... SHE'S SAFE.

14:31.662 --> 14:33.455
HERE WE GO, PENNY.

14:33.539 --> 14:35.457
{\an3}HERE WE GO NOW, I'M READY TO
RIDE THE ROLLER COASTER.

14:35.541 --> 14:38.836
{\an3}LAST CAR, THIRD FROM THE FRONT,
INSIDE SEAT, PLEASE.

14:38.919 --> 14:40.129
HEY, COULD YOU HOLD MY KEYS?

14:40.212 --> 14:41.130
AND MY COMPASS AND MY POPCORN?

14:41.213 --> 14:43.507
{\an3}AND MY LUCKY RABBIT
AND MY SWISS ARMY KNIFE?

14:43.591 --> 14:44.758
{\an3}AND MY RAISINS
AND MY HAND BUZZER?

14:44.842 --> 14:47.803
[SIGHS] STEP UP TO THE SIGN.

14:47.886 --> 14:49.346
[GRUNTS]

14:49.430 --> 14:52.850
{\an1}SORRY, LITTLE DUDE,
YOU'RE TOO SHORT.

14:52.933 --> 14:56.145
JUST A 16th OF AN INCH TOO.

14:56.228 --> 14:57.187
WHAT?

14:57.271 --> 14:58.397
WHAT?

14:58.480 --> 14:59.648
16th OF... NO...

14:59.732 --> 15:03.902
NO, NO, I WILL NOT ACCEPT THIS.

15:03.986 --> 15:06.780
YOU'RE, THIS,
THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.

15:06.864 --> 15:10.492
THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING,
WHAT, HOW...

15:10.576 --> 15:12.202
Portia: SORRY, "MESSY."

15:12.286 --> 15:16.540
{\an5}LOOKS LIKE YOU'LL HAVE TO
LOSER IT UP ON
THE LIL' PUN. [LAUGHS]

15:16.624 --> 15:18.334
Riders: AWESOME.

15:18.417 --> 15:21.003
{\an1}[LAUGHTER]

15:26.675 --> 15:28.010
[CHEERING]

15:28.093 --> 15:29.845
Girl: I'M FINALLY LIVING.

15:29.928 --> 15:33.265
Portia: SHORT PEOPLE
GOT NO REASON.

15:33.349 --> 15:35.267
[SCREAMING AND CHEERING]

15:35.351 --> 15:37.770
OH, CRAZY WORLD.

15:37.853 --> 15:39.229
MIXED-UP THINGS.

15:39.313 --> 15:41.523
[MUTTERS INDISTINCTLY]

15:41.607 --> 15:44.485
[GRUNTING]

15:44.568 --> 15:47.863
COME ON, PULL, PULL...

15:47.946 --> 15:49.448
THROW YOUR BACK INTO IT.

15:49.531 --> 15:52.034
[CREAKING NOISE]

15:52.117 --> 15:54.328
[GRUNTING]

15:54.411 --> 15:55.454
PLEASE, PLEASE.

15:55.537 --> 15:58.207
PLEASE, PLEASE.

15:58.290 --> 16:00.793
{\an3}I NEED THIS,
I REALLY, REALLY NEED THIS.

16:00.876 --> 16:02.461
NICE TRY, SMALL FRY.

16:02.544 --> 16:05.255
MM... FRIES.

16:05.339 --> 16:08.967
YOU, SIR, ARE CRUEL.

16:09.051 --> 16:09.927
Girl: AGAIN.

16:10.010 --> 16:11.720
Riders: AGAIN, AGAIN, AGAIN...

16:11.804 --> 16:13.972
AGAIN, AGAIN, AGAIN.

16:14.056 --> 16:16.684
[SCREAMS AND LAUGHS]

16:16.767 --> 16:18.644
THAT WAS AWESOME.

16:18.727 --> 16:23.190
[GRUNTING...]

16:25.442 --> 16:28.987
[BOTH GRUNTING]

16:29.071 --> 16:29.196
[GRUNTING]

16:42.668 --> 16:44.795
STILL TOO SHORT.

16:44.878 --> 16:46.505
[SIGHS]

16:46.588 --> 16:50.759
[♪...]

16:50.843 --> 16:54.096
Bessie: OK, GUYS, COAST CLEAR.

16:57.349 --> 16:59.351
OK, OK, HERE WE GO.

16:59.435 --> 17:00.853
GO-TIME, HAPPY.

17:00.936 --> 17:02.521
[GRUNTS]

17:02.604 --> 17:05.232
{\an3}[GRUNTING]

17:05.315 --> 17:07.693
BESSIE...

17:09.987 --> 17:11.905
HI, HELLO. [LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

17:11.989 --> 17:13.198
JUST, YOU KNOW, UH,
STRETCHING THE OLD LEGS.

17:15.784 --> 17:16.535
OK, HERE WE GO.

17:16.617 --> 17:19.621
THIRD TIME'S THE CHARM.

17:19.704 --> 17:24.585
HAPPY, IF ANYTHING HAPPENS,
I BEQUEATH TO YOU THE HIVE.

17:24.667 --> 17:25.210
YOU CAN HAVE MY FLIP-FLOPS.

17:25.294 --> 17:26.712
YES.

17:26.795 --> 17:30.632
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

17:35.137 --> 17:37.514
IT'S WORKING.

17:37.598 --> 17:40.225
IT'S WORKING.

17:40.309 --> 17:42.811
[GRUNTING]

17:47.357 --> 17:49.860
[GROANS]

17:49.943 --> 17:51.695
{\an3}[LAUGHS] AND THEY SAID
IT COULDN'T BE DONE.

17:51.779 --> 17:55.073
I FEEL TOTALLY NORMAL.

17:55.157 --> 17:57.868
{\an3}AND THEN YOU SAID,
"TOO SMALL, SMALL FRY."

17:57.951 --> 17:59.912
AND WE LAUGHED ABOUT THE FRIES.

17:59.995 --> 18:04.708
{\an1}ACTUALLY, I SAID,
"NICE TRY, SMALL FRY."

18:04.792 --> 18:09.671
{\an4}LOOK, IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA OFFER
ME ANY OF YOUR FRENCH FRIES,
STOP TALKING ABOUT 'EM.

18:09.755 --> 18:12.424
FRENCH FRIES?

18:12.508 --> 18:13.467
BUT I DON'T HAVE ANY.

18:13.550 --> 18:15.552
{\an3}LISTEN...

18:15.636 --> 18:17.638
YOU HAVE TO LET ME ON.

18:17.721 --> 18:20.849
BECAUSE LOOK AT ME,
NOW I'M TALL ENOUGH, HEY.

18:20.933 --> 18:24.311
HEY, I'M TALL ENOUGH TO REACH
THAT BALLOON IF I REALLY...

18:24.394 --> 18:26.188
COME HERE, BALLOON.

18:26.271 --> 18:29.191
[GRUNTING]

18:29.274 --> 18:31.527
GET OVER HERE, BALLOON.

18:31.610 --> 18:34.822
[GRUNTING]

18:35.697 --> 18:37.699
AGAIN, AGAIN, AGAIN.

18:37.783 --> 18:40.828
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

18:40.911 --> 18:43.330
LET ME MAKE IT UP TO YOU
ABOUT THE FRIES.

18:43.413 --> 18:45.958
[SIGHS]

18:46.041 --> 18:50.754
TICKET, FRY, TICKET, FRY.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.756
TICKET, FRY...

18:52.840 --> 18:55.342
{\an5}[SCREAMING]

18:52.840 --> 18:55.342
[GONG RINGS]

18:59.471 --> 19:01.306
PLAY IT COOL, HAPPY.

19:01.390 --> 19:05.561
{\an3}REMEMBER, WE ARE FROM JAPAN,
WE ARE FROM JAPAN.

19:09.565 --> 19:11.400
OH, BOY.

19:11.483 --> 19:13.694
{\an3}[GRUNTING]

19:13.777 --> 19:18.991
FOR ORIGINALITY, A ZERO.

19:19.074 --> 19:20.742
[SIGHS] PLEASE.

19:20.826 --> 19:25.247
{\an6}YOU CAN'T DO THIS,
YOU CAN'T JUST DISASSEMBLE
MY NATIONAL COSTUME.

19:25.330 --> 19:26.248
{\an3}OOH.

19:26.331 --> 19:26.915
I HAVE RIGHTS.

19:26.999 --> 19:30.878
I DEMAND TO RIDE THIS RIDE.

19:30.961 --> 19:33.380
I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE.

19:34.798 --> 19:36.133
COME ON, HAPPY.

19:36.216 --> 19:38.510
{\an3}LET'S GO RIDE
THE STUPID TEACUPS.

19:38.594 --> 19:40.095
[WHINES]

19:40.178 --> 19:42.055
[GROWLS AND GRUNTS]

19:42.139 --> 19:45.100
{\an1}HEY, DUDES, COME A LITTLE
CLOSER TO MY MOUTH.

19:45.183 --> 19:46.018
COME ON, COME ON.

19:46.101 --> 19:50.230
{\an1}GOTTA TELL YOU
SOMETHING, SERIOUSLY.

19:51.982 --> 19:52.399
Bessie: HAPPY, WHAT ARE YOU...

19:54.735 --> 19:55.777
{\an1}WHAT'S UP?

19:55.861 --> 19:59.406
[GROWLS AND BARKS]

19:59.489 --> 20:02.743
{\an1}DUDE, I'M SORRY IF
I OFFENDED YOU, MAN.

20:02.826 --> 20:05.120
{\an1}YOU REALLY DON'T NEED TO
TELL MY BOSS, OK?

20:05.203 --> 20:07.122
{\an1}I MEAN, LET'S BE,
LET'S BE COOL ABOUT THIS.

20:07.205 --> 20:10.334
[GROWLS]

20:10.417 --> 20:13.503
{\an4}LOOK, MAN, SEE, THIS JOB
IS WAY MORE STRESSFUL
THAN IT LOOKS, OK?

20:13.587 --> 20:16.757
{\an4}I MEAN, YOU KNOW, WHAT WITH
THE TICKET-TAKING AND THE,
AND THE LEVER-PULLING.

20:16.840 --> 20:19.968
{\an5}[BARKS]

20:16.840 --> 20:19.968
{\an3}[GASPS]

20:20.052 --> 20:21.970
FINE, YOU WIN.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.847
ABSOLUTELY, PRIVATE RIDE.

20:23.931 --> 20:24.932
[WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY]

20:25.015 --> 20:25.849
[BARKS]

20:25.933 --> 20:27.267
I HEARD YOU, I HEARD YOU.

20:27.351 --> 20:29.061
LAST CAR, LAST CAR.

20:30.437 --> 20:31.939
[RIDERS GROANING]

20:32.022 --> 20:33.815
OUT OF THE CAR, LADIES.

20:33.899 --> 20:36.568
V.I.P. COMING THROUGH.

20:36.652 --> 20:41.114
[GROANING...]

20:41.198 --> 20:43.742
LIKE, ONE MORE TIME, PLEASE.

20:43.825 --> 20:47.996
OW, MY TUMMY.

20:51.708 --> 20:55.796
HAPPY, YOU WERE SO ASSERTIVE.

20:55.879 --> 20:59.299
{\an6}OK, EXCUSE ME, SIR, I THINK
SOMEONE LEFT THEIR CHEWED-UP
HOT DOG PIECES IN HERE...

21:01.760 --> 21:03.637
{\an3}NEVER MIND.

21:03.720 --> 21:05.347
HERE IT IS, HAPPY.

21:05.430 --> 21:07.015
{\an3}THE MOMENT WE'VE BEEN
TRAINING FOR.

21:07.099 --> 21:09.559
{\an6}NOW WE'RE PROBABLY GONNA DO
A LOT OF SCREAMING, SO LET'S DO
SOME VOCAL WARM-UPS.

21:09.643 --> 21:12.062
{\an3}[SCREAMING]

21:12.145 --> 21:13.939
{\an1}[HOWLING]

21:14.022 --> 21:15.983
{\an3}WHOA...

21:16.066 --> 21:16.608
GO-GO-GO-GO-GO.

21:16.692 --> 21:19.152
{\an1}[BARKING]

21:19.236 --> 21:20.862
{\an3}WHOA...

21:20.946 --> 21:23.031
{\an1}[HOWLING]

21:23.115 --> 21:25.033
{\an3}WHOA...

21:25.117 --> 21:27.953
{\an1}[HOWLING]

21:28.036 --> 21:29.788
{\an3}MEOW.

21:28.036 --> 21:29.788
{\an1}[GROWLS]

21:29.871 --> 21:32.666
{\an1}KEEP YOUR HANDS IN
THE VEHICLE AT ALL TIMES.

21:32.749 --> 21:34.918
DO NOT DISENGAGE THE SAFETY BAR.

21:35.002 --> 21:36.586
YOU PUKE, YOU CLEAN IT.

21:36.670 --> 21:39.589
HAVE A GOOD RIDE.

21:39.673 --> 21:43.218
Bessie: OH, ISN'T THIS
AWESOME, HAPPY?

21:43.301 --> 21:45.178
OOH, THIS CERTAINLY IS AWESOME.

21:49.641 --> 21:50.976
OH, BOY, HAPPY.

21:51.059 --> 21:54.062
NO TURNING BACK NOW.

21:54.146 --> 21:56.898
[GASPS] THIS IS IT.

21:56.982 --> 22:03.864
[SCREAMING...]

22:08.326 --> 22:13.582
[SCREAMING...]

22:18.170 --> 22:22.758
[SCREAMING...]

22:27.888 --> 22:31.099
[HAPPY WHINES]

22:31.850 --> 22:34.519
[HAPPY WHINES]

22:34.603 --> 22:37.647
HEY, A FRENCH FRY.

22:37.731 --> 22:41.068
[SCREAMING...]

22:41.151 --> 22:43.945
LET ME OFF, I'M GONNA FALL...

22:44.029 --> 22:46.698
[SCREAMING]

22:46.782 --> 22:47.532
PRETTY SWEET, HUH?

22:53.205 --> 22:57.042
[BESSIE VOMITS]

22:57.125 --> 22:58.585
AWESOME!

22:58.960 --> 23:02.464
[♪...]

23:39.709 --> 23:40.627
[LAUGHTER]
